President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 2 through May 8, 2010, as National Charter Schools Week in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of education in shaping the future of the nation and recognizes charter schools as laboratories for innovative teaching and learning methods. The proclamation calls for support for high-quality charter schools and the replication of effective education models. It also highlights the need to provide all students with access to a complete and competitive education to empower them to achieve their dreams and lead the country in the global marketplace. The proclamation concludes by commending charter schools, teachers, and administrators, and calling on states and communities to support charter schools and the students they serve.